template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-oklahoma
name: Employee Restrictive Covenant (Oklahoma)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  Oklahoma-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement centered on
  confidentiality, trade secret protection, property return, non-disparagement,
  and narrowly drafted customer and employee non-solicitation. Omits any
  employee covenant not to compete, because Okla. Stat. tit. 15, § 217 voids
  every contract restraining a person from exercising a lawful profession,
  trade, or business of any kind, save for the narrow statutory carve-outs in §§
  218-219 (sale of goodwill and partnership dissolution) and §§ 219A-219B. The
  agreement preserves only the covenants those sections leave standing for an
  employee: a customer non-solicitation covenant drafted to reach only the
  direct solicitation of the sale of goods or services from the former
  employer's established customers, as § 219A(A) permits and no further; an
  employee anti-raiding covenant that § 219B removes from the restraint-of-trade
  prohibition; and confidentiality, trade-secret, property-return, and
  non-disparagement obligations that restrain the misuse of information rather
  than the exercise of a trade. Both non-solicits are keyed to a defined
  Restricted Period and expressly disclaim any bar on Employee working for a
  competitor. Drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel review.
