      No default is supplied because the effective date is transaction-specific.
      The field should be completed from the parties' signing or intended start
      date rather than inferred from Oklahoma law.
  - name: governing_law
    type: string
    description: >-
      Governing law state. For an employee who resides and works in Oklahoma, an
      Oklahoma forum court will not apply chosen foreign law where doing so
      violates Oklahoma's public policy against restraints on work, so an
      Oklahoma selection is the one most likely to operate as written for an
      Oklahoma employee-restrictive-covenant dispute heard in Oklahoma.
    display_label: Governing Law
    default: Oklahoma
    section: Legal
    rationale_source: case_law
    requirement_id: >-
      REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.oklahoma.treat-out-of-state-forum-selection-as-the-operative-risk
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Oklahoma is the correct default for an Oklahoma employee because the
      governing-law choice should align with the forum most likely to apply
      Oklahoma's public-policy limits rather than invite an out-of-state law
      fight.
  - name: governing_venue
    type: string
    description: >-
      County and state whose courts are the agreed forum. A mandatory
      out-of-state forum clause is the operative enforcement risk in Oklahoma: a
      court applying another state's law may enforce a covenant Oklahoma would
      void, so an Oklahoma forum keeps the dispute before a court expected to
      apply Oklahoma's void rule.
    display_label: Venue
    default: the state courts located in Oklahoma
    section: Legal
    rationale_source: case_law
    requirement_id: >-
      REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.oklahoma.treat-out-of-state-forum-selection-as-the-operative-risk
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Oklahoma state courts are the default venue because the key enforcement
      risk is transfer to an out-of-state forum that may apply another state's
      law to covenants Oklahoma would treat as void.
  - name: confidentiality_trade_secret_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of confidentiality obligations for trade secrets
    display_label: Trade Secrets Duration
