  - name: nondisparagement_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of the non-disparagement covenant
    display_label: Non-Disparagement Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Non-Disparagement
  - name: customer_nonsolicit_duration
    type: string
    description: >-
      Duration of the customer non-solicitation restriction, measured from the
      end of employment. This is a surviving covenant that Oklahoma permits only
      to the extent it bars direct solicitation of established customers.
      Oklahoma fixes no statutory maximum, so keep it reasonable under the
      common-law rule of reason; practitioners commonly use two years or less.
    display_label: Customer Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 12 months
    rationale_source: benchmark
    benchmark_ref: restrictive-covenant/customer-non-solicit-duration
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is the most common customer non-solicit term in benchmarked,
      publicly-filed employee agreements, edging out 24 months by only a narrow
      margin. Oklahoma supplies no statutory maximum, but the term should remain
      reasonable and comfortably within the commonly used two-years-or-less
      drafting range.
  - name: covered_customer_period
    type: string
    description: >-
      Look-back window before termination used to bound the class of Covered
      Customers to the established customers of the employer the employee
      actually dealt with. Section 219A(A) ties the permitted restriction to the
      established customers of the former employer, so the class is tied to a
      stated look-back window rather than reaching prospective or former
      customers.
    display_label: Covered Customer Look-Back
    default: 12 months
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
  - name: employee_nonsolicit_duration
    type: string
    description: >-
      Duration of the employee anti-raiding (no-poach) restriction, measured
      from the end of employment. Oklahoma removes an employee-solicitation
      covenant from the restraint-of-trade prohibition; keep it finite and
      workforce-relationship-protective and measure its length against the rule
      of reason.
    display_label: Employee Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    rationale_source: benchmark
    benchmark_ref: restrictive-covenant/employee-non-solicit-duration
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Oklahoma permits the solicitation-focused covenant shape but does not set
      a duration. 24 months matches the modal employee non-solicit term observed
      in benchmarked, publicly-filed employee agreements; 12 months is the
      common lighter alternative, and counsel should shorten or justify the
      period based on the workforce relationship being protected.
  - name: covered_employee_period
    type: string
    description: >-
      Look-back window before termination used to bound the class of Covered
      Employees to colleagues the employee actually worked with or supervised. A
      workforce-wide class adds nothing protective; Oklahoma protects against
      soliciting the business's employees and independent contractors.
    display_label: Covered Employee Look-Back
    default: 12 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    rationale_source: editorial
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is a conservative look-back window that keeps the covered class
      tied to employees and independent contractors with a recent workplace
      connection to Employee rather than the entire workforce.
omitted_clauses: drop
